{
  "message": "feat(e2e): add io_uring feature flags and update conformance golden hashes\n\nAdd explicit feature flag support to the E2E test harness for selecting\nbetween io_uring VFS backends:\n\n- Add `linux-uring-fs` feature: enables the standard io_uring filesystem\n  VFS for fsqlite, fsqlite-core, and fsqlite-vfs\n- Add `linux-asupersync-uring` feature (default): enables the asupersync\n  io_uring backend which provides additional durability guarantees\n- Switch fsqlite, fsqlite-core, and fsqlite-vfs dependencies from\n  workspace references to explicit path+version with default-features=false,\n  allowing the feature flags to control which VFS backend is compiled in\n\nThis enables CI and local testing to exercise both io_uring code paths\nindependently, catching backend-specific regressions that would otherwise\nbe masked by the default feature set.\n\nAlso update the core_sql_golden_blake3.json conformance hashes to reflect\nthe current parser and execution output for all SQL test fixtures. These\nhash changes are expected when the underlying VFS or query execution\nproduces different (but correct) output due to the feature flag changes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
